  "summary": [
    "Make bulk-imported ChatGPT replies first-class editable workspace drafts instead of mislabelled archive records",
    "Repair existing imported replies and link them to their source batch and item during migration",
    "Load imported drafts in Reply Editor even when the linked Helpdesk ticket exists but has an empty reply field",
    "Persist local edits before remote Helpdesk synchronization so network failures never discard reviewer work",
    "Detect differing local and Helpdesk drafts as an explicit conflict without silently overwriting either version",
    "Keep approved and issued revisions immutable and separate from mutable imported working drafts",
    "Expose source batch, filename, source row, version and synchronization state in the editor and batch details",
    "Add queue status and statistics for Imported Draft, synchronization failure and synchronization conflict",
    "Add end-to-end regression tests for CSV import through Reply Editor visibility, editing, sync failure and conflict handling",
    "Run complete Python tests, migration verification and Astro production build during normal installation"
  ],
